description.narrative:
AENA work on facilitation and advocacy of sustainable use, management and governance of natural resources (empowering communities for dialogue with the investing company). They have operations in the Nampula and Zambezia province dealing with Land.
Thiscampaign is poised to achieve multiple objectives, firstly by equipping small-scale farmers and the Mozambicans citizens to secure long term commitment from parliamentarians to adopt regulations for smallholder farmers can be successfully and sustainableintegrated into restructured and liberalized markets through contracts with supermarkets, secondly by increasing spaces for accountability and politicalcommitment and thirdly by incorporating a robust learning approach to document processes and tools onhow change happens.
the main AENA's task is to enable effective engagement of all stakeholders at all levels: advocacy, development plans and implementation. It aims to increase the participation of civil society and communities in decision-making and establish a link to learning at higher levels. the main Key strategies: are: lobby meetings with parliamentarians [Committee for Agriculture, Economic and Environment] and policy makers; Lobby meetings with supermarkets;lobby meetings with policy makers; Policy briefing papers; Media, publications and public debates;
